theorem Topology.boundary_compl_eq_boundary {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure ((A : Set X)ᶜ) \ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) =
      closure (A : Set X) \ interior A := by
  -- Relate `closure` and `interior` of complements to those of the original set.
  have h_cl :
      closure ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (interior (A : Set X))ᶜ :=
    Topology.closure_compl_eq_compl_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  have h_int :
      interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ :=
    Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Rewrite and simplify the boundary of the complement.
  calc
    closure ((A : Set X)ᶜ) \ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ)
        = (interior (A : Set X))ᶜ ∩ closure (A : Set X) := by
          simp [h_cl, h_int, Set.diff_eq, Set.compl_compl, Set.inter_comm]
    _ = closure (A : Set X) ∩ (interior (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
          simpa [Set.inter_comm]
    _ = closure (A : Set X) \ interior (A : Set X) := by
          simpa [Set.diff_eq, Set.inter_comm]

theorem Set.compl_compl {α : Type*} (s : Set α) : sᶜᶜ = s := by
  ext x
  simp
